            <property name="styleSheet">
             <string notr="true">font: 600 9pt 'Segoe UI'; color: #6b7280; letter-spacing: 1px;</string>
            </property>
            <property name="text">
             <string>Given resistance values and a target low cutoff frequency, this page finds the required capacitor values.

For individual capacitor values:
C = 1 / (2π R fL)

If the question says:
C1 = C2 = CE

Use the common-capacitor formula:
Ccommon = Σ(1/Ri) / (2π fL)

The smallest resistance is only the dominant point. The exact common capacitor value uses all given resistance points.</string>
            </property>
           </widget>
          </item>
