          </item>
          <item>
           <widget class="QLabel" name="labelFormulaText">
            <property name="sizePolicy">
             <sizepolicy hsizetype="Preferred" vsizetype="Fixed">
              <horstretch>0</horstretch>
              <verstretch>0</verstretch>
             </sizepolicy>
            </property>
            <property name="styleSheet">
             <string notr="true">QLabel {
    color: rgb(80, 80, 80);                  /* soft dark gray */
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Roboto&quot;, sans-serif;
}</string>
            </property>
            <property name="text">
             <string>LOW-FREQUENCY CAPACITOR FINDER

Individual capacitor values:
C1 = 1 / (2π R11 fL)
C2 = 1 / (2π R22 fL)
C3 = 1 / (2π R33 fL)
CE = 1 / (2π REE fL)
CE1 = 1 / (2π REE1 fL)
CE2 = 1 / (2π REE2 fL)

Use this when the question asks for each capacitor separately.

Common capacitor value:
If the question says C1 = C2 = CE = C, then:

fL ≈ f1 + f2 + fE

and:

f1 = 1 / (2π R11 C)
f2 = 1 / (2π R22 C)
fE = 1 / (2π REE C)

Therefore:

Ccommon = [1/R11 + 1/R22 + 1/REE] / (2π fL)

General form:

Ccommon = Σ(1/Ri) / (2π fL)

The smallest resistance is only the dominant point.
It is not the full common-capacitor formula.</string>
            </property>
            <property name="wordWrap">
             <bool>true</bool>
            </property>
           </widget>
